There is a chance though, that one of the admin moved this post from the General board to the Rant board for that reason, but left Ealan01's message on it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 3:56:08 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: STRIKE! Lets make one last effort fellow Wizards.</span><hr size=1> Strikes?  In the months since June 99 when I started Grimstaff I have seen 4 sit ins, more than a dozen petitions, dozens of strike calls, lots of people saying we shouldn't port to the planes, etc.  None of it amounts to anything.  Part of the reason is that people really don't play their Wizard that much (there may be a bunch on a server, but rarely are they on at the same time, and too often only for special events and teleports) and that most are just too busy or disinterested in some 'event' that Verant will ignore.  Wizards are fiercely independent types.  Part of this is enforced by Verant's bizarre concept for the class (selfish), and part of it I think is just the mindset that makes a Wizard.<br>
<br>
But I think the real reason strikes and such don't work is that we know deep down they won't make a damn bit of difference.  Seriously, what happens if we refuse to port to the planes?  One or two will anyway, crossing the 'picket lines' to help their guild, thus negating the effect (just how many people go to the planes any given day anyway?).  But the real problem is that we are pretty crippled.  If we don't port people, Druids will and charge 10% more for the monopoly.  If we don't port to the planes, who the heck cares?  We only go to two of them anyway.<br>
<br>
I understand the sentiment (all too well) that makes people call for strikes.  I sympathise with the attitude.  But it wouldn't really change anything, even if enough people DID try. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=166.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=163.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.threadControl?topicID=159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=159.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=159.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilation